{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"You know, one of the intense pleasures of travel"},{"time":3000,"text":"and one of the delights of ethnographic research"},{"time":5000,"text":"is the opportunity to live amongst those"},{"time":7000,"text":"who have not forgotten the old ways,"},{"time":9000,"text":"who still feel their past in the wind,"},{"time":12000,"text":"touch it in stones polished by rain,"},{"time":15000,"text":"taste it in the bitter leaves of plants."},{"time":17000,"text":"Just to know that Jaguar shamans still journey beyond the Milky Way,"},{"time":21000,"text":"or the myths of the Inuit elders still resonate with meaning,"},{"time":25000,"text":"or that in the Himalaya,"},{"time":28000,"text":"the Buddhists still pursue the breath of the Dharma,"},{"time":32000,"text":"is to really remember the central revelation of anthropology,"},{"time":35000,"text":"and that is the idea that the world in which we live"},{"time":38000,"text":"does not exist in some absolute sense,"},{"time":40000,"text":"but is just one model of reality,"},{"time":41000,"text":"the consequence of one particular set of adaptive choices"},{"time":45000,"text":"that our lineage made, albeit successfully, many generations ago."}]},{"cues":[{"time":50000,"text":"And of course, we all share the same adaptive imperatives."},{"time":54000,"text":"We're all born. We all bring our children into the world."},{"time":56000,"text":"We go through initiation rites."},{"time":58000,"text":"We have to deal with the inexorable separation of death,"},{"time":60000,"text":"so it shouldn't surprise us that we all sing, we all dance,"},{"time":64000,"text":"we all have art."}]},{"cues":[{"time":66000,"text":"But what's interesting is the unique cadence of the song,"},{"time":69000,"text":"the rhythm of the dance in every culture."},{"time":71000,"text":"And whether it is the Penan in the forests of Borneo,"},{"time":74000,"text":"or the Voodoo acolytes in Haiti,"},{"time":78000,"text":"or the warriors in the Kaisut desert of Northern Kenya,"},{"time":84000,"text":"the Curandero in the mountains of the Andes,"},{"time":87000,"text":"or a caravanserai in the middle of the Sahara --"},{"time":92000,"text":"this is incidentally the fellow that I traveled into the desert with"},{"time":94000,"text":"a month ago --"},{"time":95000,"text":"or indeed a yak herder in the slopes of Qomolangma,"},{"time":98000,"text":"Everest, the goddess mother of the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":100000,"text":"All of these peoples teach us that there are other ways of being,"},{"time":103000,"text":"other ways of thinking,"},{"time":104000,"text":"other ways of orienting yourself in the Earth."},{"time":106000,"text":"And this is an idea, if you think about it,"},{"time":108000,"text":"can only fill you with hope."},{"time":110000,"text":"Now, together the myriad cultures of the world"},{"time":113000,"text":"make up a web of spiritual life and cultural life"},{"time":117000,"text":"that envelops the planet,"},{"time":119000,"text":"and is as important to the well-being of the planet"},{"time":121000,"text":"as indeed is the biological web of life that you know as a biosphere."},{"time":124000,"text":"And you might think of this cultural web of life"},{"time":127000,"text":"as being an ethnosphere,"},{"time":128000,"text":"and you might define the ethnosphere"},{"time":130000,"text":"as being the sum total of all thoughts and dreams, myths,"},{"time":133000,"text":"ideas, inspirations, intuitions brought into being"},{"time":136000,"text":"by the human imagination since the dawn of consciousness."},{"time":140000,"text":"The ethnosphere is humanity's great legacy."},{"time":143000,"text":"It's the symbol of all that we are"},{"time":145000,"text":"and all that we can be as an astonishingly inquisitive species."}]},{"cues":[{"time":150000,"text":"And just as the biosphere has been severely eroded,"},{"time":153000,"text":"so too is the ethnosphere"},{"time":155000,"text":"-- and, if anything, at a far greater rate."},{"time":157000,"text":"No biologists, for example, would dare suggest"},{"time":159000,"text":"that 50 percent of all species or more have been or are"},{"time":162000,"text":"on the brink of extinction because it simply is not true,"},{"time":164000,"text":"and yet that -- the most apocalyptic scenario"},{"time":166000,"text":"in the realm of biological diversity --"},{"time":169000,"text":"scarcely approaches what we know to be the most optimistic scenario"},{"time":172000,"text":"in the realm of cultural diversity."},{"time":174000,"text":"And the great indicator of that, of course, is language loss."}]},{"cues":[{"time":177000,"text":"When each of you in this room were born,"},{"time":180000,"text":"there were 6,000 languages spoken on the planet."},{"time":183000,"text":"Now, a language is not just a body of vocabulary"},{"time":186000,"text":"or a set of grammatical rules."},{"time":188000,"text":"A language is a flash of the human spirit."},{"time":190000,"text":"It's a vehicle through which the soul of each particular culture"},{"time":193000,"text":"comes into the material world."},{"time":194000,"text":"Every language is an old-growth forest of the mind,"},{"time":197000,"text":"a watershed, a thought, an ecosystem of spiritual possibilities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":201000,"text":"And of those 6,000 languages, as we sit here today in Monterey,"},{"time":205000,"text":"fully half are no longer being whispered into the ears of children."},{"time":209000,"text":"They're no longer being taught to babies,"},{"time":212000,"text":"which means, effectively, unless something changes,"},{"time":214000,"text":"they're already dead."},{"time":215000,"text":"What could be more lonely than to be enveloped in silence,"},{"time":219000,"text":"to be the last of your people to speak your language,"},{"time":221000,"text":"to have no way to pass on the wisdom of the ancestors"},{"time":224000,"text":"or anticipate the promise of the children?"},{"time":227000,"text":"And yet, that dreadful fate is indeed the plight of somebody"},{"time":230000,"text":"somewhere on Earth roughly every two weeks,"},{"time":232000,"text":"because every two weeks, some elder dies"},{"time":234000,"text":"and carries with him into the grave the last syllables"},{"time":236000,"text":"of an ancient tongue."}]},{"cues":[{"time":238000,"text":"And I know there's some of you who say, \"Well, wouldn't it be better,"},{"time":240000,"text":"wouldn't the world be a better place"},{"time":241000,"text":"if we all just spoke one language?\" And I say, \"Great,"},{"time":244000,"text":"let's make that language Yoruba. Let's make it Cantonese."},{"time":247000,"text":"Let's make it Kogi.\""},{"time":248000,"text":"And you'll suddenly discover what it would be like"},{"time":250000,"text":"to be unable to speak your own language."}]},{"cues":[{"time":253000,"text":"And so, what I'd like to do with you today"},{"time":256000,"text":"is sort of take you on a journey through the ethnosphere,"},{"time":260000,"text":"a brief journey through the ethnosphere,"},{"time":262000,"text":"to try to begin to give you a sense of what in fact is being lost."},{"time":267000,"text":"Now, there are many of us who sort of forget"},{"time":274000,"text":"that when I say \"different ways of being,\""},{"time":276000,"text":"I really do mean different ways of being."}]},{"cues":[{"time":279000,"text":"Take, for example, this child of a Barasana in the Northwest Amazon,"},{"time":284000,"text":"the people of the anaconda"},{"time":285000,"text":"who believe that mythologically they came up the milk river"},{"time":287000,"text":"from the east in the belly of sacred snakes."},{"time":290000,"text":"Now, this is a people who cognitively"},{"time":293000,"text":"do not distinguish the color blue from the color green"},{"time":295000,"text":"because the canopy of the heavens"},{"time":297000,"text":"is equated to the canopy of the forest"},{"time":298000,"text":"upon which the people depend."},{"time":300000,"text":"They have a curious language and marriage rule"},{"time":303000,"text":"which is called \"linguistic exogamy:\""},{"time":305000,"text":"you must marry someone who speaks a different language."},{"time":308000,"text":"And this is all rooted in the mythological past,"},{"time":310000,"text":"yet the curious thing is in these long houses,"},{"time":312000,"text":"where there are six or seven languages spoken"},{"time":314000,"text":"because of intermarriage,"},{"time":316000,"text":"you never hear anyone practicing a language."},{"time":319000,"text":"They simply listen and then begin to speak."}]},{"cues":[{"time":322000,"text":"Or, one of the most fascinating tribes I ever lived with,"},{"time":324000,"text":"the Waorani of northeastern Ecuador,"},{"time":328000,"text":"an astonishing people first contacted peacefully in 1958."},{"time":331000,"text":"In 1957, five missionaries attempted contact"},{"time":335000,"text":"and made a critical mistake."},{"time":336000,"text":"They dropped from the air"},{"time":337000,"text":"8 x 10 glossy photographs of themselves"},{"time":339000,"text":"in what we would say to be friendly gestures,"},{"time":341000,"text":"forgetting that these people of the rainforest"},{"time":343000,"text":"had never seen anything two-dimensional in their lives."},{"time":346000,"text":"They picked up these photographs from the forest floor,"},{"time":348000,"text":"tried to look behind the face to find the form or the figure,"},{"time":351000,"text":"found nothing, and concluded that these were calling cards"},{"time":353000,"text":"from the devil, so they speared the five missionaries to death."},{"time":357000,"text":"But the Waorani didn't just spear outsiders."},{"time":359000,"text":"They speared each other."},{"time":360000,"text":"54 percent of their mortality was due to them spearing each other."},{"time":363000,"text":"We traced genealogies back eight generations,"},{"time":366000,"text":"and we found two instances of natural death"},{"time":368000,"text":"and when we pressured the people a little bit about it,"},{"time":370000,"text":"they admitted that one of the fellows had gotten so old"},{"time":372000,"text":"that he died getting old, so we speared him anyway. (Laughter)"},{"time":376000,"text":"But at the same time they had a perspicacious knowledge"},{"time":379000,"text":"of the forest that was astonishing."},{"time":380000,"text":"Their hunters could smell animal urine at 40 paces"},{"time":383000,"text":"and tell you what species left it behind."}]},{"cues":[{"time":386000,"text":"In the early '80s, I had a really astonishing assignment"},{"time":388000,"text":"when I was asked by my professor at Harvard"},{"time":390000,"text":"if I was interested in going down to Haiti,"},{"time":393000,"text":"infiltrating the secret societies"},{"time":395000,"text":"which were the foundation of Duvalier's strength"},{"time":397000,"text":"and Tonton Macoutes,"},{"time":398000,"text":"and securing the poison used to make zombies."},{"time":401000,"text":"In order to make sense out of sensation, of course,"},{"time":404000,"text":"I had to understand something about this remarkable faith"},{"time":407000,"text":"of Vodoun. And Voodoo is not a black magic cult."},{"time":410000,"text":"On the contrary, it's a complex metaphysical worldview."},{"time":413000,"text":"It's interesting."},{"time":414000,"text":"If I asked you to name the great religions of the world,"},{"time":415000,"text":"what would you say?"},{"time":416000,"text":"Christianity, Islam, Buddhism, Judaism, whatever."}]},{"cues":[{"time":419000,"text":"There's always one continent left out,"},{"time":421000,"text":"the assumption being that sub-Saharan Africa"},{"time":423000,"text":"had no religious beliefs. Well, of course, they did"},{"time":425000,"text":"and Voodoo is simply the distillation"},{"time":428000,"text":"of these very profound religious ideas"},{"time":429000,"text":"that came over during the tragic Diaspora of the slavery era."},{"time":432000,"text":"But, what makes Voodoo so interesting"},{"time":434000,"text":"is that it's this living relationship"},{"time":436000,"text":"between the living and the dead."},{"time":437000,"text":"So, the living give birth to the spirits."},{"time":438000,"text":"The spirits can be invoked from beneath the Great Water,"},{"time":441000,"text":"responding to the rhythm of the dance"},{"time":443000,"text":"to momentarily displace the soul of the living,"},{"time":445000,"text":"so that for that brief shining moment, the acolyte becomes the god."},{"time":449000,"text":"That's why the Voodooists like to say"},{"time":451000,"text":"that \"You white people go to church and speak about God."},{"time":454000,"text":"We dance in the temple and become God.\""},{"time":456000,"text":"And because you are possessed, you are taken by the spirit --"},{"time":459000,"text":"how can you be harmed?"},{"time":460000,"text":"So you see these astonishing demonstrations:"},{"time":463000,"text":"Voodoo acolytes in a state of trance"},{"time":465000,"text":"handling burning embers with impunity,"},{"time":468000,"text":"a rather astonishing demonstration of the ability of the mind"},{"time":471000,"text":"to affect the body that bears it"},{"time":472000,"text":"when catalyzed in the state of extreme excitation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":476000,"text":"Now, of all the peoples that I've ever been with,"},{"time":478000,"text":"the most extraordinary are the Kogi"},{"time":480000,"text":"of the Sierra Nevada de Santa Marta in northern Colombia."},{"time":483000,"text":"Descendants of the ancient Tairona civilization"},{"time":486000,"text":"which once carpeted the Caribbean coastal plain of Colombia,"},{"time":489000,"text":"in the wake of the conquest,"},{"time":490000,"text":"these people retreated into an isolated volcanic massif"},{"time":493000,"text":"that soars above the Caribbean coastal plain."},{"time":495000,"text":"In a bloodstained continent,"},{"time":497000,"text":"these people alone were never conquered by the Spanish."},{"time":500000,"text":"To this day, they remain ruled by a ritual priesthood"},{"time":503000,"text":"but the training for the priesthood is rather extraordinary."},{"time":506000,"text":"The young acolytes are taken away from their families"},{"time":508000,"text":"at the age of three and four,"},{"time":510000,"text":"sequestered in a shadowy world of darkness"},{"time":512000,"text":"in stone huts at the base of glaciers for 18 years:"},{"time":516000,"text":"two nine-year periods"},{"time":517000,"text":"deliberately chosen to mimic the nine months of gestation"},{"time":520000,"text":"they spend in their natural mother's womb;"},{"time":522000,"text":"now they are metaphorically in the womb of the great mother."},{"time":525000,"text":"And for this entire time,"},{"time":527000,"text":"they are inculturated into the values of their society,"},{"time":530000,"text":"values that maintain the proposition that their prayers"},{"time":532000,"text":"and their prayers alone maintain the cosmic --"},{"time":535000,"text":"or we might say the ecological -- balance."},{"time":538000,"text":"And at the end of this amazing initiation,"},{"time":539000,"text":"one day they're suddenly taken out"},{"time":541000,"text":"and for the first time in their lives, at the age of 18,"},{"time":544000,"text":"they see a sunrise. And in that crystal moment of awareness"},{"time":548000,"text":"of first light as the Sun begins to bathe the slopes"},{"time":551000,"text":"of the stunningly beautiful landscape,"},{"time":553000,"text":"suddenly everything they have learned in the abstract"},{"time":555000,"text":"is affirmed in stunning glory. And the priest steps back"},{"time":558000,"text":"and says, \"You see? It's really as I've told you."},{"time":560000,"text":"It is that beautiful. It is yours to protect.\""},{"time":563000,"text":"They call themselves the \"elder brothers\""},{"time":565000,"text":"and they say we, who are the younger brothers,"},{"time":568000,"text":"are the ones responsible for destroying the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":572000,"text":"Now, this level of intuition becomes very important."},{"time":574000,"text":"Whenever we think of indigenous people and landscape,"},{"time":576000,"text":"we either invoke Rousseau"},{"time":578000,"text":"and the old canard of the \"noble savage,\""},{"time":581000,"text":"which is an idea racist in its simplicity,"},{"time":583000,"text":"or alternatively, we invoke Thoreau"},{"time":586000,"text":"and say these people are closer to the Earth than we are."},{"time":588000,"text":"Well, indigenous people are neither sentimental"},{"time":590000,"text":"nor weakened by nostalgia."},{"time":592000,"text":"There's not a lot of room for either"},{"time":594000,"text":"in the malarial swamps of the Asmat"},{"time":596000,"text":"or in the chilling winds of Tibet, but they have, nevertheless,"},{"time":599000,"text":"through time and ritual, forged a traditional mystique of the Earth"},{"time":603000,"text":"that is based not on the idea of being self-consciously close to it,"},{"time":606000,"text":"but on a far subtler intuition:"},{"time":608000,"text":"the idea that the Earth itself can only exist"},{"time":612000,"text":"because it is breathed into being by human consciousness."}]},{"cues":[{"time":614000,"text":"Now, what does that mean?"},{"time":616000,"text":"It means that a young kid from the Andes"},{"time":618000,"text":"who's raised to believe that that mountain is an Apu spirit"},{"time":620000,"text":"that will direct his or her destiny"},{"time":622000,"text":"will be a profoundly different human being"},{"time":625000,"text":"and have a different relationship to that resource"},{"time":628000,"text":"or that place than a young kid from Montana"},{"time":630000,"text":"raised to believe that a mountain is a pile of rock"},{"time":633000,"text":"ready to be mined."},{"time":634000,"text":"Whether it's the abode of a spirit or a pile of ore is irrelevant."},{"time":638000,"text":"What's interesting is the metaphor that defines the relationship"},{"time":641000,"text":"between the individual and the natural world."},{"time":643000,"text":"I was raised in the forests of British Columbia"},{"time":645000,"text":"to believe those forests existed to be cut."},{"time":647000,"text":"That made me a different human being"},{"time":649000,"text":"than my friends amongst the Kwagiulth"},{"time":651000,"text":"who believe that those forests were the abode of Huxwhukw"},{"time":653000,"text":"and the Crooked Beak of Heaven"},{"time":654000,"text":"and the cannibal spirits that dwelled at the north end of the world,"},{"time":657000,"text":"spirits they would have to engage during their Hamatsa initiation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":661000,"text":"Now, if you begin to look at the idea"},{"time":663000,"text":"that these cultures could create different realities,"},{"time":665000,"text":"you could begin to understand"},{"time":666000,"text":"some of their extraordinary discoveries. Take this plant here."},{"time":671000,"text":"It's a photograph I took in the Northwest Amazon just last April."},{"time":673000,"text":"This is ayahuasca, which many of you have heard about,"},{"time":676000,"text":"the most powerful psychoactive preparation"},{"time":679000,"text":"of the shaman's repertoire."},{"time":681000,"text":"What makes ayahuasca fascinating"},{"time":683000,"text":"is not the sheer pharmacological potential of this preparation,"},{"time":687000,"text":"but the elaboration of it. It's made really of two different sources:"},{"time":691000,"text":"on the one hand, this woody liana"},{"time":693000,"text":"which has in it a series of beta-carbolines,"},{"time":695000,"text":"harmine, harmaline, mildly hallucinogenic --"},{"time":698000,"text":"to take the vine alone"},{"time":700000,"text":"is rather to have sort of blue hazy smoke"},{"time":702000,"text":"drift across your consciousness --"},{"time":704000,"text":"but it's mixed with the leaves of a shrub in the coffee family"},{"time":707000,"text":"called Psychotria viridis."},{"time":709000,"text":"This plant had in it some very powerful tryptamines,"},{"time":712000,"text":"very close to brain serotonin, dimethyltryptamine,"},{"time":716000,"text":"5-methoxydimethyltryptamine."},{"time":717000,"text":"If you've ever seen the Yanomami"},{"time":719000,"text":"blowing that snuff up their noses,"},{"time":721000,"text":"that substance they make from a different set of species"},{"time":724000,"text":"also contains methoxydimethyltryptamine."},{"time":728000,"text":"To have that powder blown up your nose"},{"time":730000,"text":"is rather like being shot out of a rifle barrel"},{"time":734000,"text":"lined with baroque paintings and landing on a sea of electricity. (Laughter)"},{"time":741000,"text":"It doesn't create the distortion of reality;"},{"time":743000,"text":"it creates the dissolution of reality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":744000,"text":"In fact, I used to argue with my professor, Richard Evan Shultes --"},{"time":747000,"text":"who is a man who sparked the psychedelic era"},{"time":749000,"text":"with his discovery of the magic mushrooms"},{"time":751000,"text":"in Mexico in the 1930s --"},{"time":753000,"text":"I used to argue that you couldn't classify these tryptamines"},{"time":755000,"text":"as hallucinogenic because by the time you're under the effects"},{"time":758000,"text":"there's no one home anymore to experience a hallucination. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":762000,"text":"But the thing about tryptamines is they cannot be taken orally"},{"time":765000,"text":"because they're denatured by an enzyme"},{"time":767000,"text":"found naturally in the human gut called monoamine oxidase."},{"time":770000,"text":"They can only be taken orally if taken in conjunction"},{"time":773000,"text":"with some other chemical that denatures the MAO."},{"time":776000,"text":"Now, the fascinating things"},{"time":777000,"text":"are that the beta-carbolines found within that liana"},{"time":781000,"text":"are MAO inhibitors of the precise sort necessary"},{"time":785000,"text":"to potentiate the tryptamine. So you ask yourself a question."},{"time":788000,"text":"How, in a flora of 80,000 species of vascular plants,"},{"time":792000,"text":"do these people find these two morphologically unrelated plants"},{"time":796000,"text":"that when combined in this way,"},{"time":797000,"text":"created a kind of biochemical version"},{"time":799000,"text":"of the whole being greater than the sum of the parts?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":801000,"text":"Well, we use that great euphemism, \"trial and error,\""},{"time":804000,"text":"which is exposed to be meaningless."},{"time":806000,"text":"But you ask the Indians, and they say, \"The plants talk to us.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":809000,"text":"Well, what does that mean?"},{"time":810000,"text":"This tribe, the Cofan, has 17 varieties of ayahuasca,"},{"time":814000,"text":"all of which they distinguish a great distance in the forest,"},{"time":818000,"text":"all of which are referable to our eye as one species."},{"time":822000,"text":"And then you ask them how they establish their taxonomy"},{"time":824000,"text":"and they say, \"I thought you knew something about plants."},{"time":827000,"text":"I mean, don't you know anything?\" And I said, \"No.\""},{"time":829000,"text":"Well, it turns out you take each of the 17 varieties"},{"time":832000,"text":"in the night of a full moon, and it sings to you in a different key."},{"time":835000,"text":"Now, that's not going to get you a Ph.D. at Harvard,"},{"time":837000,"text":"but it's a lot more interesting than counting stamens. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":841000,"text":"Now --"},{"time":842000,"text":"(Applause) --"},{"time":845000,"text":"the problem -- the problem is that even those of us"},{"time":847000,"text":"sympathetic with the plight of indigenous people"},{"time":849000,"text":"view them as quaint and colorful"},{"time":850000,"text":"but somehow reduced to the margins of history"},{"time":852000,"text":"as the real world, meaning our world, moves on."},{"time":855000,"text":"Well, the truth is the 20th century, 300 years from now,"},{"time":857000,"text":"is not going to be remembered for its wars"},{"time":860000,"text":"or its technological innovations,"},{"time":861000,"text":"but rather as the era in which we stood by"},{"time":864000,"text":"and either actively endorsed or passively accepted"},{"time":866000,"text":"the massive destruction of both biological and cultural diversity"},{"time":869000,"text":"on the planet. Now, the problem isn't change."},{"time":872000,"text":"All cultures through all time"},{"time":874000,"text":"have constantly been engaged in a dance"},{"time":877000,"text":"with new possibilities of life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":879000,"text":"And the problem is not technology itself."},{"time":882000,"text":"The Sioux Indians did not stop being Sioux"},{"time":884000,"text":"when they gave up the bow and arrow"},{"time":885000,"text":"any more than an American stopped being an American"},{"time":887000,"text":"when he gave up the horse and buggy."},{"time":889000,"text":"It's not change or technology"},{"time":890000,"text":"that threatens the integrity of the ethnosphere. It is power,"},{"time":894000,"text":"the crude face of domination."},{"time":896000,"text":"Wherever you look around the world,"},{"time":898000,"text":"you discover that these are not cultures destined to fade away;"},{"time":901000,"text":"these are dynamic living peoples"},{"time":903000,"text":"being driven out of existence by identifiable forces"},{"time":906000,"text":"that are beyond their capacity to adapt to:"},{"time":908000,"text":"whether it's the egregious deforestation"},{"time":911000,"text":"in the homeland of the Penan --"},{"time":913000,"text":"a nomadic people from Southeast Asia, from Sarawak --"},{"time":916000,"text":"a people who lived free in the forest until a generation ago,"},{"time":920000,"text":"and now have all been reduced to servitude and prostitution"},{"time":923000,"text":"on the banks of the rivers,"},{"time":925000,"text":"where you can see the river itself is soiled with the silt"},{"time":929000,"text":"that seems to be carrying half of Borneo away"},{"time":931000,"text":"to the South China Sea,"},{"time":932000,"text":"where the Japanese freighters hang light in the horizon"},{"time":934000,"text":"ready to fill their holds with raw logs ripped from the forest --"},{"time":938000,"text":"or, in the case of the Yanomami,"},{"time":939000,"text":"it's the disease entities that have come in,"},{"time":941000,"text":"in the wake of the discovery of gold."}]},{"cues":[{"time":943000,"text":"Or if we go into the mountains of Tibet,"},{"time":945000,"text":"where I'm doing a lot of research recently,"},{"time":948000,"text":"you'll see it's a crude face of political domination."},{"time":951000,"text":"You know, genocide, the physical extinction of a people"},{"time":953000,"text":"is universally condemned, but ethnocide,"},{"time":956000,"text":"the destruction of people's way of life, is not only not condemned,"},{"time":959000,"text":"it's universally, in many quarters, celebrated"},{"time":962000,"text":"as part of a development strategy."},{"time":964000,"text":"And you cannot understand the pain of Tibet"},{"time":967000,"text":"until you move through it at the ground level."},{"time":969000,"text":"I once travelled 6,000 miles from Chengdu in Western China"},{"time":973000,"text":"overland through southeastern Tibet to Lhasa"},{"time":976000,"text":"with a young colleague, and it was only when I got to Lhasa"},{"time":980000,"text":"that I understood the face behind the statistics"},{"time":983000,"text":"you hear about:"},{"time":984000,"text":"6,000 sacred monuments torn apart to dust and ashes,"},{"time":988000,"text":"1.2 million people killed by the cadres"},{"time":991000,"text":"during the Cultural Revolution."},{"time":993000,"text":"This young man's father had been ascribed to the Panchen Lama."},{"time":995000,"text":"That meant he was instantly killed"},{"time":997000,"text":"at the time of the Chinese invasion."},{"time":999000,"text":"His uncle fled with His Holiness in the Diaspora"},{"time":1001000,"text":"that took the people to Nepal."},{"time":1004000,"text":"His mother was incarcerated"},{"time":1006000,"text":"for the crime of being wealthy."},{"time":1009000,"text":"He was smuggled into the jail at the age of two"},{"time":1011000,"text":"to hide beneath her skirt tails"},{"time":1013000,"text":"because she couldn't bear to be without him."},{"time":1015000,"text":"The sister who had done that brave deed"},{"time":1017000,"text":"was put into an education camp."},{"time":1018000,"text":"One day she inadvertently stepped on an armband"},{"time":1021000,"text":"of Mao, and for that transgression,"},{"time":1023000,"text":"she was given seven years of hard labor."},{"time":1026000,"text":"The pain of Tibet can be impossible to bear,"},{"time":1029000,"text":"but the redemptive spirit of the people is something to behold."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1033000,"text":"And in the end, then, it really comes down to a choice:"},{"time":1036000,"text":"do we want to live in a monochromatic world of monotony"},{"time":1039000,"text":"or do we want to embrace a polychromatic world of diversity?"},{"time":1042000,"text":"Margaret Mead, the great anthropologist, said, before she died,"},{"time":1045000,"text":"that her greatest fear was that as we drifted towards"},{"time":1048000,"text":"this blandly amorphous generic world view"},{"time":1050000,"text":"not only would we see the entire range of the human imagination"},{"time":1055000,"text":"reduced to a more narrow modality of thought,"},{"time":1059000,"text":"but that we would wake from a dream one day"},{"time":1060000,"text":"having forgotten there were even other possibilities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1064000,"text":"And it's humbling to remember that our species has, perhaps,"},{"time":1067000,"text":"been around for [150,000] years."},{"time":1069000,"text":"The Neolithic Revolution -- which gave us agriculture,"},{"time":1072000,"text":"at which time we succumbed to the cult of the seed;"},{"time":1074000,"text":"the poetry of the shaman was displaced"},{"time":1076000,"text":"by the prose of the priesthood;"},{"time":1077000,"text":"we created hierarchy specialization surplus --"},{"time":1080000,"text":"is only 10,000 years ago."},{"time":1082000,"text":"The modern industrial world as we know it"},{"time":1084000,"text":"is barely 300 years old."},{"time":1086000,"text":"Now, that shallow history doesn't suggest to me"},{"time":1088000,"text":"that we have all the answers for all of the challenges"},{"time":1091000,"text":"that will confront us in the ensuing millennia."},{"time":1093000,"text":"When these myriad cultures of the world"},{"time":1095000,"text":"are asked the meaning of being human,"},{"time":1098000,"text":"they respond with 10,000 different voices."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1100000,"text":"And it's within that song that we will all rediscover the possibility"},{"time":1106000,"text":"of being what we are: a fully conscious species,"},{"time":1109000,"text":"fully aware of ensuring that all peoples and all gardens"},{"time":1112000,"text":"find a way to flourish. And there are great moments of optimism."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1118000,"text":"This is a photograph I took at the northern tip of Baffin Island"},{"time":1121000,"text":"when I went narwhal hunting with some Inuit people,"},{"time":1124000,"text":"and this man, Olayuk, told me a marvelous story of his grandfather."},{"time":1128000,"text":"The Canadian government has not always been kind"},{"time":1130000,"text":"to the Inuit people, and during the 1950s,"},{"time":1132000,"text":"to establish our sovereignty, we forced them into settlements."},{"time":1135000,"text":"This old man's grandfather refused to go."},{"time":1139000,"text":"The family, fearful for his life, took away all of his weapons,"},{"time":1143000,"text":"all of his tools."},{"time":1145000,"text":"Now, you must understand that the Inuit did not fear the cold;"},{"time":1147000,"text":"they took advantage of it."},{"time":1148000,"text":"The runners of their sleds were originally made of fish"},{"time":1151000,"text":"wrapped in caribou hide."},{"time":1152000,"text":"So, this man's grandfather was not intimidated by the Arctic night"},{"time":1157000,"text":"or the blizzard that was blowing."},{"time":1159000,"text":"He simply slipped outside, pulled down his sealskin trousers"},{"time":1163000,"text":"and defecated into his hand. And as the feces began to freeze,"},{"time":1166000,"text":"he shaped it into the form of a blade."},{"time":1169000,"text":"He put a spray of saliva on the edge of the shit knife"},{"time":1171000,"text":"and as it finally froze solid, he butchered a dog with it."},{"time":1174000,"text":"He skinned the dog and improvised a harness,"},{"time":1177000,"text":"took the ribcage of the dog and improvised a sled,"},{"time":1181000,"text":"harnessed up an adjacent dog,"},{"time":1182000,"text":"and disappeared over the ice floes, shit knife in belt."},{"time":1186000,"text":"Talk about getting by with nothing. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1190000,"text":"And this, in many ways --"},{"time":1191000,"text":"(Applause) --"},{"time":1193000,"text":"is a symbol of the resilience of the Inuit people"},{"time":1195000,"text":"and of all indigenous people around the world."},{"time":1198000,"text":"The Canadian government in April of 1999"},{"time":1200000,"text":"gave back to total control of the Inuit"},{"time":1203000,"text":"an area of land larger than California and Texas put together."},{"time":1206000,"text":"It's our new homeland. It's called Nunavut."},{"time":1209000,"text":"It's an independent territory. They control all mineral resources."},{"time":1212000,"text":"An amazing example of how a nation-state"},{"time":1214000,"text":"can seek restitution with its people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1219000,"text":"And finally, in the end, I think it's pretty obvious"},{"time":1222000,"text":"at least to all of all us who've traveled"},{"time":1223000,"text":"in these remote reaches of the planet,"},{"time":1227000,"text":"to realize that they're not remote at all."},{"time":1228000,"text":"They're homelands of somebody."},{"time":1230000,"text":"They represent branches of the human imagination"},{"time":1232000,"text":"that go back to the dawn of time. And for all of us,"},{"time":1236000,"text":"the dreams of these children, like the dreams of our own children,"},{"time":1239000,"text":"become part of the naked geography of hope."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1242000,"text":"So, what we're trying to do at the National Geographic, finally,"},{"time":1246000,"text":"is, we believe that politicians will never accomplish anything."},{"time":1250000,"text":"We think that polemics --"},{"time":1251000,"text":"(Applause) --"},{"time":1253000,"text":"we think that polemics are not persuasive,"},{"time":1255000,"text":"but we think that storytelling can change the world,"},{"time":1258000,"text":"and so we are probably the best storytelling institution"},{"time":1261000,"text":"in the world. We get 35 million hits on our website every month."},{"time":1264000,"text":"156 nations carry our television channel."},{"time":1268000,"text":"Our magazines are read by millions."},{"time":1270000,"text":"And what we're doing is a series of journeys"},{"time":1273000,"text":"to the ethnosphere where we're going to take our audience"},{"time":1275000,"text":"to places of such cultural wonder"},{"time":1278000,"text":"that they cannot help but come away dazzled"},{"time":1280000,"text":"by what they have seen, and hopefully, therefore,"},{"time":1282000,"text":"embrace gradually, one by one,"},{"time":1285000,"text":"the central revelation of anthropology:"},{"time":1287000,"text":"that this world deserves to exist in a diverse way,"},{"time":1291000,"text":"that we can find a way to live"},{"time":1292000,"text":"in a truly multicultural, pluralistic world"},{"time":1295000,"text":"where all of the wisdom of all peoples"},{"time":1297000,"text":"can contribute to our collective well-being."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1300000,"text":"Thank you very much."},{"time":1301000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}